name: Pat Ryan 🇺🇸
tweet_text: Candidates from service backgrounds frequently face barriers to entry when running - whether a lack of institutional support, financing, or even the tools to run a strong campaign. This is doubly true for state and local candidates, and I experienced this myself when I first ran.

name: Pat Ryan 🇺🇸
tweet_text: That's what motivated me to start @servenypac - to help many of the same folks who have worked to guide our communities through this crisis continue to serve in elected office.

name: Pat Ryan 🇺🇸
tweet_text: In a year of unprecedented challenge and hardship, I saw local leaders across our state step up in extraordinary ways to care for their communities. At the same time, we've seen some of the most violent and disgusting rhetoric at the national level, culminating with Jan. 6th

name: Pat Ryan 🇺🇸
tweet_text: I fervently reject the removal of these services and am calling on HealthAlliance to act quickly to honor its commitment to ensuring our community’s health and safety and bring back these services immediately.

name: Pat Ryan 🇺🇸
tweet_text: Permanently closing these beds, especially in the middle of a surging opioid and mental-health crisis precipitated by a once-in-a-century pandemic, is completely unacceptable. This destructive move comes after HealthAlliance received over $90 million in taxpayer-funded support.

name: Pat Ryan 🇺🇸
tweet_text: I warned WMC CEO several months ago that the loss of these critical behavioral health services in Ulster County would prove “utterly devastating to our community.” Tragically, these fears have proven true. Substance use fatalities are up 91% and suicide deaths have doubled.

name: Pat Ryan 🇺🇸
tweet_text: Longtime nurses and staff have been laid off or forced to work in far-flung locations. And, most disturbingly, HealthAlliance has now made clear that they have no intention of returning any of these inpatient beds.

name: Pat Ryan 🇺🇸
tweet_text: Six months later, it’s clear that both of those promises have been broken. My office has received dozens of calls from families who are confused, angry, and not able to get the care they need for their loved ones...

name: Pat Ryan 🇺🇸
tweet_text: In early April, HAHV shut down 60 inpatient behavioral health beds to make room for a potential Covid-19 specialized care center. We were assured this would be a temporary move and that there was a well-conceived plan to keep delivering vital behavioral-health services.

name: Pat Ryan 🇺🇸
tweet_text: HealthAlliance must fully & immediately reactivate the inpatient behavioral health beds they closed earlier this year. We can’t allow #COVID19 to detract from our efforts to address the equally critical opioid and mental-health crises impacting our county. https://t.co/YubeBZIHjl
